                            handLaTeX Release Notes

   Sylvain Fourmanoit
   <[1]syfou@users.sourceforge.net>
   version 1.0.0

   Latest version of this document is available [2]here. Project homepage is
   [3]there.

What is handLaTex?

   handLatex makes it easy to inject automated, pseudo-random variations in
   [4]LaTeX documents' output reproducing the typical quirks of a left to
   right, top to bottom handwriting. It has two components:

    1. a LaTeX package, hand, that can be included in any valid LaTeX
       document.

    2. a specialized command-line frontend, handlatex, able to process LaTeX
       documents using the hand package.

Requirements

     * A working TeX distribution, supporting LaTeX 2e (originally developped
       on [5]TeX Live)

     * [6]Python 2.5.x

Installation

     * The hand package (composed of the files hand.dtx, hand.ins and
       hand.def) should be installed as any other LaTeX package, following
       your local TeX distribution's documentation.

     * handlatex should be installed as any other Python module, using the
       provided distutils script (setup.py). Typical invokation will be, with
       proper privileges:

 python setup.py install

Usage

   The hand package comes fully documented: you can usually get a local
   version of the manual by invoking your favorite LaTeX driver on hand.dtx.
   The lasted version can be found pre-compiled [7]here, in [8]PDF.

   Once you have a valid LaTeX document using hand, you can compile it by
   invoking handlatex on it. For the sake of completeness, below is
   reproduced its manual page (handlatex.1).

   handLaTeX Command Line Frontend Manual Page

 HANDLATEX(1)                     User Commands                    HANDLATEX(1)



 NAME
        handlatex - manual page for handlatex 1.0.0

 SYNOPSIS
        handlatex [options] input_file

 DESCRIPTION
        Process the LaTeX input_file with the handwriting driver.

 OPTIONS
        --version
               show program's version number and exit

        -h, --help
               show this help message and exit

        --lowwordangle=LOWWORDANGLE
               force  lowwordangle option (see hand package doc; default value:
               -2)

        --maxparscale=MAXPARSCALE
               force maxparscale option (see hand package doc;  default  value:
               1.25)

        --minparscale=MINPARSCALE
               force  minparscale  option (see hand package doc; default value:
               0.8)

        --encoding=ENCODING
               force encoding option (see  hand  package  doc;  default  value:
               utf-8)

        --highwordangle=HIGHWORDANGLE
               force highwordangle option (see hand package doc; default value:
               2)

        --driver=DRIVER
               force driver option (see hand package doc; default value: latex)

        --minparangle=MINPARANGLE
               force  minparangle  option (see hand package doc; default value:
               -2)

        --freqword=FREQWORD
               force freqword option (see hand package doc; default value: 0.4)

        --maxparangle=MAXPARANGLE
               force  maxparangle  option (see hand package doc; default value:
               2)

